                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "H"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is a finite dimensional Hilbert space, then the weak convergence implies convergence. Give a counter example to show that weak convergence does not necessarily imply convergence in an infinite dimensional Hilbert space. "
